visitor

Class SymbolTableVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • visitor.SymbolTableVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Visitor

    public class SymbolTableVisitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements Visitor
    Objects of the class SymbolTableVisitor are used to traverse an abstract syntax tree for some Minijava program (in a depth-first manner) in order to fill the corresponding symbol table. Note: the implementation includes no error handling

      • putVariable

        private void putVariable(java.lang.String varname,
                         java.lang.String type,
                         int offset)
        stores the given variable name (and its type and offset) in the symbol table. If the process is currently within a method scope the variable is stored as a local variable of the current method. If no method scope is entered the variable is stored as a global variable of the current class. TODO (UG): cast should be omitted
        Parameters:
        varname -
        type -
        offset -

      • convertType

        private java.lang.String convertType(Type type)
        converts a node of the syntax tree of type "Type" into a string. This string will be stored in the symbol table. - If type corresponds to a user-defined class, the name of the class is returned. - If the type is a predefined type then either "IntegerType", "BooleanType", "IntArrayType" is returned. - If no type is given "VoidType" is returned
        Parameters:
        type -
        Returns:
        String representation of the given type
